main event: A possible satellite was observed overhead at 35N 174W in the Pacific on March 6, 1964.
interesting points: The object was sighted from a military source at 07:55Z GMT.
The object was observed traveling from north to south.
The altitude and speed of the object were unknown.
The case was reported as a probable satellite observation.
The report indicates that no EPIC (Electronic Processing of Information Center) data was available.
